FeedPackage.Description:
Xamarin.Android Bindings for Google Play Services - Maps
With the Google Maps Android API, you can add maps based on Google Maps data to your application. The API automatically handles access to Google Maps servers, data downloading, map display, and response to map gestures. You can also use API calls to add markers, polygons, and overlays to a basic map, and to change the user's view of a particular map area. These objects provide additional information for map locations, and allow user interaction with the map.

FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.GooglePlayServices.Maps

Xamarin.Android Bindings for Google Play Services - Nearby
Nearby exposes simple publish and subscribe methods that rely on proximity. Your app publishes a payload that can be received by nearby subscribers. On top of this foundation, you can build a variety of user experiences to share messages and create real-time connections between nearby devices.

FeedPackage.Description: A BDD/TDD framework based on xUnit.net and inspired by Gherkin. Allows features and scenarios to be written directly in code rather than mapping to external feature files. Works seamlessly with xUnit.net tooling. Installing this package installs Xbehave.Core and xunit.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: https://github.com/xbehave/xbehave.net/releases
FeedPackage.Tags: xUnit.net BDD test TDD
FeedPackage.Title: Xbehave

FeedPackage.Description: Includes the libraries for writing tests with xBehave.net. Installing this package installs xunit.core.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
### New * Based on xUnit.net 2.0 and supports all new xUnit.net 2.0 features. * `x()`, an alternative to `f()` and `_()`.\*
### Changed * When a step fails, all following steps in the scenario are reported as skipped. In xBehave.net 1.x, all following steps in the scenario were reported as failed. * The `Before()` and `After()` methods of a `BeforeAfterTestAttribute` are now called before and after each scenario is run. In xBehave.net 1.x, these methods were called before and after each step within a scenario was run. * [[Object disposal]] and [[Teardown]] are no longer represented as a separate test unless they fail. This aligns with the behaviour of most xUnit.net 2.0 runners which show an extra failed test when test clean up fails.
### Removed * `Given()`, `When()`, `Then()`, `And()` and `But()`. Use `f()`, `_()` or `x()`\* instead. * [[Timeouts]] have been removed under the same rationale used for [xUnit.net 2.0](http://xunit.github.io/docs/test-migration.html). * [[Isolated steps]] have been removed as this is a rarely (if ever) used feature that adds considerable implementation overhead. * [[Object disposal]] without passing a context object to `Using()` (deprecated in 1.x). * An undocumented feature which allows global continuation of step execution when certain types of step fail. * An undocumented feature which allows omission of arguments from scenario names in test output.
\* *Work in progress - not yet provided in the current pre-release package.*
* rc-002: added Xbehave.Core package * rc-001: switched steps following a failed step from failed to skipped, added x(), tweaked messaging behaviour * beta-008: Fixed NCrunch support and re-introduced BeforeAfterTest support. * beta-007: Fixed Resharper runner support and removed flawed BeforeAfterTest support. * beta-006: Fixed VS runner support. * beta-005: Updated to xunit 2.0.0 (stable) and restricted platform support to .NET 4.5 only. * beta-004: Fixed test output for steps which are failed fast due to failure of preceding steps. * beta-003: Fixed test class construction and disposal and changed behaviour of BeforeAfterTestAttribute. * beta-002: Added support for Windows 8.1+ (Universal), Windows Phone 8 (Silverlight), Windows Phone 8.1+ (Universal). * beta-001: Initial beta.
FeedPackage.Tags: xUnit.net BDD test TDD

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Essentials is the core part of the toolkit that deals with reading and writing IFC data files. It does not contain support for geometric operations and 3D visualation. Use xBIM 3D if you need support for geometry and presentation, its also open source. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats and will convert models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures. A range of 3D viewing controls are provided for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: This version builds for Any CPU.
FeedPackage.Summary: The .Net toolkit for developing BIM applications based on the IFC standard.
FeedPackage.Tags: BIM IFC IfcXml IfcZip COBie .Net C# BuildingSmart

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Essentials is the core part of the toolkit that deals with reading and writing IFC data files. It does not contain support for geometric operations and 3D visualisation. Use xBIM 3D if you need support for geometry and presentation, its also open source. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.

All programmatic access to Ifc Entities is through a single interface, allowing one code base to work with all Ifc formats. Ifc4 is the default interface future proofing your development work. This release replaces Xbim Essentials 3 but minor code reafactoring will be required, XbimModel is deprecated in favour of IfcStore.

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Essentials is the core part of the toolkit that deals with reading and writing IFC data files. It does not contain support for geometric operations and 3D visualisation. Use xBIM 3D if you need support for geometry and presentation, its also open source. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). 3.0 contains a new geometry engine that has a full API to allow geometry constructions, boolean operations and meshing. It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Now references net40 framework and provides signed dlls.

FeedPackage.Description:
XbimTeam have changed the approach to the Nuget packages ID.
Xbim.Essentials.4 has been discontinued, but an alternative is available; the alternative package is called "Xbim.Essentials". To install it, you can proceed as follows:
Case 1: If you want to install Xbim.Essentials support from scratch in your solution. Search and install the "Xbim.Essentials" package instead.
Case 2: If you have already installed this version. Issue the following command in the Package Manager Console window:
Uninstall-Package Xbim.Essentials.4 –Force
Afterwards you should still have Xbim.Essentials package in your solution.
You can safely delete this file and the XbimUpdate folder in your solution.

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Exchange is the COBie, COBieLite and other Exchange based Xbim libraries. These suppport interoperation with other BIM Standards. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Exchange is the COBie, COBieLite and other Exchange based Xbim libraries. These suppport interoperation with other BIM Standards. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: 4.0 contains the code ported to the multiple schema infrastructure of Xbim.Essentials 4.
FeedPackage.Summary: The .Net toolkit for developing BIM applications based on the IFC standard. Essential support for the Ifc data model

FeedPackage.Description: Basic 2D game library for indie games.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Removed the ICommand list from the ScriptCompiler and used the "ImplementationManager" instead. Removed the handle from the "GraphicsDevice". Made the "LibraryLoader" a default component. Extended the "ObjectStorage" so you can configure whether or not to parse strings. Improved some little things like "readonly" and unneded usings. Removed the unneeded ICondition interface. Improved our Component system. Removed the now unneeded ValueProvider and implemented a system where you can mark your interfaces with an attribute and the instances will be registered as these interfaces. Removed an "error" in the GlobalExceptionHandler. The event handler is getting called twice. Improved the "CryptographyHelper". Removed the "EventSubject" class and moved the code directly into the EventManager. Improved our scene system. Implemented lag compensation options inside the gameloop, fixed a bug inside our network engine. Improved our network system.

id: 51c70cda-9217-11e6-ae22-56b6b6499611 title: Xamarin.UITest 2.0.1
## Improvements
* Added `IApp.SwipeRightToLeft()` and `IApp.SwipeLeftToRight()` for use in web views. * [iOS] `withInertia` can be set to false for `Scroll*` methods when using iOS10. * [iOS] Fix issue where tests fail when using `.AppBundle()` with paths containing a space. * [Android] Workaround for apps where manifest as reported by `aapt dump xmltree` is invalid. * [Android] Android Test Server updated to 0.8.4. * [Android] Fixed occasional failure detecting devices after connecting a new device. * `test-cloud.exe --fixture` parameter now also accepts a class name without a namespace.

## Improvements
* Added overload of `AppQuery.Id()` which takes an `int id` parameter. FeedPackage.Description:
Wrapper of the ObjectAnimator that can be used similarly to ViewPropertyAnimator.
ViewPropertyObjectAnimator is as easy to use as ViewPropertyAnimator and (unlike ViewPropertyAnimator) lets you utilize all the awesome features that ObjectAnimator allows (e.g. it can be used inside AnimatorSet).
Additionally ViewPropertyObjectAnimator lets you animate View's dimensions, padding, margin and scroll.
FeedPackage.Summary: Wrapper of the ObjectAnimator that can be used similarly to ViewPropertyAnimator.
FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.ViewPropertyObjectAnimator

FeedPackage.Description: xBIM Exchange is the COBie, COBieLite and other Exchange based Xbim libraries. These suppport interoperation with other BIM Standards. xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: 4.0 contains the code ported to the multiple schema infrastructure of Xbim.Essentials 4.
FeedPackage.Summary: The .Net toolkit for developing BIM applications based on the IFC standard. Essential support for the Ifc data model
FeedPackage.Tags: BIM IFC IfcXml IfcZip COBie COBieLite .Net C# BuildingSmart

FeedPackage.Description:
XbimTeam have changed the approach to the Nuget packages ID.
Xbim.Exchange.4 has been discontinued, but an alternative is available; the alternative package is called "Xbim.Exchange". To install it, you can proceed as follows:
Case 1: If you want to install Xbim.Exchange support from scratch in your solution. Search and install the "Xbim.Exchange" package instead.
Case 2: If you have already installed this version. Issue the following commands in the Package Manager Console window:
Uninstall-Package Xbim.Exchange.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Geometry.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Essentials.4 –Force
Afterwards you should still have Xbim.Exchange package in your solution.
You can safely delete this file and the XbimUpdate folder in your solution.

XbimTeam have changed the approach to the Nuget packages ID.
Xbim.Geometry.4 has been discontinued, but an alternative is available; the alternative package is called "Xbim.Geometry". To install it, you can proceed as follows:
Case 1: If you want to install Xbim.Geometry support from scratch in your solution. Search and install the "Xbim.Geometry" package instead.
Case 2: If you have already installed this version. Issue the following commands in the Package Manager Console window:
Uninstall-Package Xbim.Geometry.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Essentials.4 –Force
Afterwards you should still have Xbim.Geometry package in your solution.
You can safely delete this file and the XbimUpdate folder in your solution.

The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.

FeedPackage.Description:
XbimTeam have changed the approach to the Nuget packages ID.
Xbim.WindowsUI.4 has been discontinued, but an alternative is available; the alternative package is called "Xbim.WindowsUI". To install it, you can proceed as follows:
Case 1: If you want to install Xbim.WindowsUI support from scratch in your solution. Search and install the "Xbim.WindowsUI" package instead.
Case 2: If you have already installed this version. Issue the following commands in the Package Manager Console window:
Uninstall-Package Xbim.WindowsUI.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Exchange.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Geometry.4 –Force Uninstall-Package Xbim.Essentials.4 –Force
Afterwards you should still have Xbim.WindowsUI package in your solution.
You can safely delete this file and the XbimUpdate folder in your solution.

FeedPackage.Description:
WeXplorer is the visualization part of xBIM toolkit that deals with vizualization of IFC data on web using preprocessed wexBIM file. It uses cutting edge web technologies like WebGL so it is not supposed to work in old browsers but should work very well with Chrome or Mozzilla since 2011, IE11 and others with support for this technology. Use xBIM Essentials and xBIM Geometry to create optimalized and compressed wexBIM files for vizualization.
xBIM is an Open Source Toolkit for developing IFC based applications (BuildingSmart Data model). It provides full support for reading and writing geometry, topology and data in accordance with the Ifc2x3 schema. xBIM reads and writes Ifc, IfcXMl and IfcZip formats. The xBIM project provides packages to convert IFC models to COBie spreadsheets in both UK and US cultures as well as a range of 3D viewing controls for use with Windows forms, WPF, WEBGL and OpenGL platforms. IOS and Android versions are under development.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Initial release

FeedPackage.Description:
Xamarin.Android Bindings for Google Play Services - Vision
The Face API finds human faces in photos, videos, or live streams. It also finds and tracks positions of facial landmarks such as the eyes, nose, and mouth.
The API also provides information about the state of facial features -- are the subject's eyes open? Are they smiling? With these technologies, you can edit photos and video, enhance video feeds with effects and decorations, create hands-free controls for games and apps, or react when a person winks or smiles.
The Barcode Scanner API detects barcodes in real time in any orientation. You can also detect and parse several barcodes in different formats at the same time.
